headline: Tyson yet to feel impact from Nebraska plant closure as beef volumes decline
summary: "Looking forward, we expect cattle supplies to remain tight throughout 2026 and 2027," said president and CEO Donnie King.

headline: Tyson Customers Flock to Chicken While Beef Flounders
summary: Thankfully, consumers have simply flocked to chicken in lieu of steak, keeping the company afloat and helping it beat Wall Street’s estimates.
